Benefits:
  - Machines can detect prohibited items in public transport automatically.
  - Can be utilized in airports or in general public travel services.
  - Can be used to automate cars; they can be programmed to recognise traffic and pedestrians.

Limitations
  - May not be 100% accurate/reliable.
  - May not be suited to public environments as they are crowded - objects can obstruct each other from view.

Risks
  - Being too reliant on the machine can cause safety issues if it stops functioning.
